text: El cast es perfecto! 😱🤩 Hero hace al Hardin perfecto y Josephine es hermosa como Tessa. Es estresante ver cuanta gente ha estado criticando la saga desde que se anunció la película. Es decir, hello! Todos sabemos que es una relación tóxica, UFF inmensamente, pero no hay que negar que a veces hay momentos lindos entre los personajes; además, a medida que avanzan los libros, se desarrollan más los personajes y logran descubrirse a sí mismos. Eso sí, la película deberían ponerla de +16, porque de ley (queramos o no) muchas dirán que influye en las mentes de las adolescentes haciéndoles creer que esa relación es la mejor. No es por ser mala, pero tendría que ser bien boba alguien para creerse o siquiera seguir el ejemplo de una PELICULA o una HISTORIA DE FICCION, sí, hay chicas que a veces se dejan nublar por cosas así, pero para eso están los padres y también los demás a sus alrededores diciéndoles lo que está bien y lo que no. Ya está en cada una si decide dejarse influenciar por una película. No está mal disfrutar de un libro que muestra una relación tóxica, no significa que yo quiera una relación así, simplemente es entretenido. Es como aquellos que leen historias o ven películas de asesinatos y cosas de terror que quieran que les suceda eso y lo hagan suceder (y si lo hay, son personas que no tienen un juicio bien desarrollado). Cada persona tiene sus gustos, pero primero ANTES  de criticar, hay que leer o ver en este caso la película y sacar conclusiones propias, sin dejarse llevar por lo que otros comentan.

text: I already wrote my comment in spansih but I also want other people to understand me 🌚 like I said, Hero makes a perfect Hardin and Josephine the most beautiful Tessa. It’s kinda annoying (and surprising) the amount of criticism that the movie is getting from some people. Okay, for a fact we all know that the After series show a toxic relationship, there’s no denying on that, but is also true that the characters develop in every book and we get to discover their true selfs. We know it is a toxic relationship, and there is nothing wrong in liking to read books like this because everyone has their own taste; just because they like the topic of the book doesn’t mean that they want that to happen for real. The movie seems to be avoiding some toxic scenes and let’s hope it changes it somehow. However, when it comes to the movie, i think it should be for girls over 17 (I think in the US they put R for restricted, I don’t know), because we trust that they know better than to get influenced by a MOVIE, a FICTIONAL STORY. Most people say that After will be bad because it encourages teenagers to find a “love” like it is portrayed there and get involved into toxic relationships. Not to be mean, but you should really be kinda dumb to believe everything that some movie shows you. That’s why only people with their minds straight should watch it. But, what it has to be clear, is that people need to read the books or watch the movie to make some valid critic, not just be based on what others say. Some people like the book, but that doesn’t mean that they identify with it or want that type of relationship for themselves. Is just for entertainment. Peace out! ✌️(no fight intented .-.)

I also spent 8 hours creating his mansion once he made a lot of money. I did use someone's mansion layout but the furniture, flowers, lighting stove, bathrooms are all created by me. I every night (once sister showed me how to keep screen from turning off) I left him on the max arrow forward and he made all the money on his own. I used 0 cheats on him. I think he would make an excellent edition to your characters. text: Hi guys, I know many of you want to see more of Harry and Tessa so I created an after 4, https://www.wattpad.com/story/172530482-after-4?utm_source=web&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share_myworks  The link is above just click on it!  I’m going to be posting a chapter every day so the whole book will be about 100 chapters, the first chapter is kind of a teaser chapter I just wanted to see if people will actually read the book. I am creating more of the Hessa relationship and I want to stay true to how Anna wrote the series bc honestly I am in love with the series and I was really sad to see it end so I want to make everyone happy(myself included) and contine on the series. I know many people do not approve of the Hessa toxic relationship but hopefully my take on the story will give you a different perspective. All credits to Anna though, she wrote an amazing series and I just want to give you guys more of the story since I know there isn’t a solid continuation of the series out there and I am going to post every day, I would love to here suggestions on my take as well. Hope everyone has a good new year and please please please it would mean the world to me if you read my take on the series. Just click on my profile and you’ll find the book. Also save it to your library and send me your comments!
